reviews.text: I entered when the rush had subsided. Woodside Cafe surrounded us with inexplicable culinary charm! The taste profiles are well-developed. Service staff were kind and knew what they were talking about. Our neighborhood is proud to host this spot.

A Woodside standard that never fails me! Friendly staff that always welcomes you warmly. Delicious fare. Pizzas are tasty. The chorizo and eggs skillet is excellent. And the burgers are always on point.

The food was great and the ambiance was lovely. However, one thing to be aware of is that the restaurant allows dogs indoors. While I personally love dogs and have one of my own, I believe there should be a level of consideration for all guests.

During our visit, the diner next to us had an open packet of wet dog food on the table and proceeded to hand-feed her dog throughout the meal. While I understand and appreciate pet-friendly spaces, this felt a bit intrusive and may be off-putting to others trying to enjoy their dining experience.

A little more mindfulness from pet owners‚Äîand perhaps clearer guidelines from the restaurant‚Äîwould go a long way in maintaining a comfortable atmosphere for everyone.

I stopped by for lunch today and had an absolutely delightful meal! I enjoyed the poached pear salad along with the fish and chips, and everything was spot on. The salad was incredibly fresh, with warm, perfectly poached pears that felt like a cozy treat on a winter day. The roasted walnuts added just the right touch of sweetness, and I loved that the dressing was balanced rather than overpowering.

The fish and chips were a true standout! The beer batter was crisp, golden, and stayed beautifully intact, complementing the tender fish inside. And the sweet potato fries‚Äîwow! Perfectly crispy, not the least bit soggy, just how they should be. It‚Äôs clear the chefs know exactly what they‚Äôre doing.

Every bite was a joy, and I can‚Äôt wait to come back for more. Thank you for an amazing meal!

The staff here needs to be more attentive and responsible. Their lack of care can lead to a very disappointing customer experience.

Live music by a talented cover singer‚Äìguitarist, tasty food prepared as orderers requested, capable of serving large parties efficiently and courteously. We had 12 people, and all of our food came out with it minutes of each other. Traditional Irish / UK pub food like bangers & mash (delicious brown gravy and onions on top of the heap of mashed potatoes, surrounded by three sausages) and fish & chips (large pieces, tender in a light batter). Also chicken tenders & French fries, spaghetti & meatballs, and, why not, bruschetta and also fish tacos, this latter with a deceivingly spicy salsa verde served on the side. Very good.
Excellent, kind and professional service all around.
Music levels kept low enough to allow for conversation (thank you !).
All around, excellent.

While my wife and I were in Queens for a weekend last month, we had dinner both evenings at the Woodside Cafe, and we would recommend this restaurant to others enthusiastically.  We both ordered the Grilled Salmon entree - twice! - (although I was tempted to try a pizza, which looked delicious, when I saw it delivered to another table), and enjoyed every bite. Our drinks - Zinfandel and draft Brooklyn Lager - were excellent. Our servers and others working in the restaurant were kind and helpful. The prices were quite moderate.
The food overall is good, but the fries really suck and I hope they can improve it, it literally just tastes like baked potatoes.

If possible try to come here for the weekday lunch special. The New England Clam Chowder and Shepard's Pie (lunch size) was great. If ordering the Shepherd's Pie take care not to touch the bowl it is served in as one can burn their hands.

Fish and chips are always crispy and hot. Chicken curry is always perfect. It was our first time trying the senorita pizza and it was very good. Woodside Cafe is a MUST go to if you‚Äôre in queens. EVERYTHING was amazing from service to food. I got the onion soup, mac and cheese skillet and philly cheese steak sandwich. Everything was literal perfection! Elias was our server and he was the most polite person ever. He checked up on us frequently and was quick. Also the woman with the butterfly tattoos on her neck.
